From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Drew Williams <drew.williams@capstanmedical.com>
Date: Tue, 12 May 2026 17:00:00 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] Snapshot m_links in OutPin destructor to avoid iterator
 invalidation on shutdown

`OutPin<T>::~OutPin` iterates `m_links` (vector<weak_ptr<Link>>) by
reference. The loop body locks each weak_ptr and calls
`right()->deleteLink()` on the downstream InPin, which resets the
InPin's `shared_ptr<Link>`. That drops the Link's last shared owner and
triggers `Link::~Link()`, which calls `m_left->deleteLink()` back into
this same OutPin. `OutPin::deleteLink` does
`m_links.erase(remove_if(... expired ...))` — mutating the vector we're
currently iterating with a range-for.

On WPILib's filter designer this manifested as a SIGSEGV at app exit
whenever any link still existed when the editor was destroyed.

Move m_links into a local snapshot first; the recursive
`m_left->deleteLink` now erases on an empty vector and is a no-op. Hold
a shared_ptr to the Link across the deleteLink call so destruction
happens at the end of the iteration body, not concurrently with the
right() call.

Signed-off-by: Drew Williams <drew.williams@capstanmedical.com>
---
 include/ImNodeFlow.h | 16 +++++++++++++++-
 1 file changed, 15 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/include/ImNodeFlow.h b/include/ImNodeFlow.h
index 68dbdaff60000000000000000000000000000000..68dbdaff60000000000000000000000000000000 100644
--- a/include/ImNodeFlow.h
+++ b/include/ImNodeFlow.h
@@ -1150,8 +1150,22 @@ namespace ImFlow

         /**
          * @brief <BR>When parent gets deleted, remove the links
-         */
-        ~OutPin() override { for (auto &l: m_links) if (!l.expired()) l.lock()->right()->deleteLink(); }
+         *
+         * The snapshot move is load-bearing: dropping the link via
+         * right()->deleteLink() destroys the Link, whose own destructor
+         * calls m_left->deleteLink() back into THIS OutPin. That
+         * deleteLink mutates m_links — and we're inside a range-for over
+         * m_links if we don't snapshot first. The move empties our
+         * member, so the recursive erase finds nothing to do.
+         */
+        ~OutPin() override {
+            auto snapshot = std::move(m_links);
+            for (auto& l: snapshot) {
+                if (auto link = l.lock()) {
+                    link->right()->deleteLink();
+                }
+            }
+        }

         /**
          * @brief <BR>Create link between pins
